Mandatory Role-Play Requirements  \par
\par
1) All Anima must choose a purpose that was unfinished in life.  This can be as much as to protect someone, Solve an unfinished task, or to harass someone you hated in life.  This purpose must be included in your SL and approved by the FD or SL Manager.  Characters may have multiple purposes if they desire but at least one of your purposes must be linked to your Anchor.\par
\par
2) Anima are not immaterial as classical ghosts are thought to be.  Their flesh and bone bodies are more resilient and stronger than any mortal's.  This is because they are fueled not by food, but by a spirit whose passion for life, for whatever reason, was stronger than the icy hand of death.  An Anima does not need to eat, sleep, or even breathe.  They do however need an Anchor, something that acts as a link between the land of the living and the hereafter.  It can be anything from a childhood toy, to a locket, or even a certain house or vehicle.   If the Touchstone is destroyed and his body is killed, the Anima loses his physical body and is doomed to wander, never to complete his task.  He is consigned for an eternity of endless, bodiless haunting.  If an Anima is more than 1 square mile from his Anchor, he begins to lose Body at a rate of 1 point per hour.  If he returns to his Anchor before he loses all of his Body, all Body points are returned instantly. If he does not return in time, then his body dies and he is trapped on this mortal coil forever.\par
\par
All Anima have connections with their previous life, these are called Anchors and solidify the Anima to this world.  All Anima have two Anchors that they must choose to hold dear to them (ST or FD Approval required).  The Anima cares for and protects these Anchors with a single minded determination for a good reason, should any of your anchors be destroyed (SL or ST Event required) Your character will permanently lose a point of Soul.  This lost point can be brought back up with XP only after a New Anchor has been found to replace the old one, showing a new puropse added to your existance.\par
